As of the [[2020 United States census]], there were 371 people, 123 households, and 64 families residing in the town.

At the publication of the [[2000 United States census]], there were 464 people, 203 households, and 132 families residing in the town.<ref name="GR2" /> The population density was {{convert|248.2|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. There were 236 housing units at an average density of {{convert|126.3|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of the town was 75.43% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 22.63% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.43% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 1.51% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 1.94% of the population.

